The paper deals with the problem of assigning orientations to edges in a planar graph while preserving distances between pairs of terminals. This problem involves graph theory, computational geometry, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
